title: Aashish Gupta
text: Broadly, my work examines interrelations between health, environment, and social inequality. A related interest is improving the measurement of demographic and development outcomes in low- and middle-income countries. My work was awarded Civil Registration and Vital Statistics Fellowship by the International Union for the Scientific Study of Population, and the Dorothy Thomas Award for best graduate student paper by the Population Association of America in 2021.
